                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.77/1494</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-26T15:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 26, 1915, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Hukuang bridge specifications, prepared by Cox, require shop erection. Managing
                    director refuses to modify, considering requirement proper. I beg to request
                    instructions as to how far to press protest and whether American manufacturers
                    are willing to guarantee fit of bridges without shop erection.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
